        "tokens": [
         {
          "text": "koseiv",
          "type": "text"
         }
        ]
       },
       {
        "text": ", “writing”) producing a sentence, “he is writing.”",
        "type": "text"
       }
      ],
      "children": []
     },
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "There is no word equivalent to “is” in Hebrew and Aramaic, so we just say “he writing” and the “is” is implied by context.",
        "type": "text"
       }
      ],
      "children": []
     },
     {
      "ordinal": "-",
      "ordered": false,
      "tokensOfLine": [
       {
        "text": "Even though the ",
